Sentencas: Understanding the sintering processes extensively is critical in fabricating a flat cell for solid oxide fuel cell stacks, but few have reported the sintering process and stress development during the constrained sintering of the electrolyte layer on anode substrate.
Titulo: Constrained sintering of Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte on anode substrate

Sentencas: In this study, we show that the green tape of half cell fabricated by co-tape casting cracks into several pieces when it is heated directly to 1400 degrees C of profile I, while it remains flat and complete when the green tape is sintered with additional pre-sintered profile at 1300 degrees C of profile II.
Titulo: Constrained sintering of Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte on anode substrate

Sentencas: The strain rate characteristics indicate that the difference of 2.43 x 10(-6) s(-1) between the electrolyte and the anode layer leads to the stress development in the directly sintered cell, while it reduces to 6.7 x 10(-8)
Titulo: Constrained sintering of Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte on anode substrate

Sentencas: s(-1) for the pre-sintered cell, which is only 3% of that without pre-sintering.
Titulo: Constrained sintering of Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte on anode substrate

Sentencas: The stress based on continuum model calculated results in the sintered cell demonstrates that the stress increases from 0 at about 1000 degrees C to 2.60 MPa at 1300 degrees C, and increased from 2.60 MPa to 6.54 MPa in temperature range of 1300-1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Constrained sintering of Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte on anode substrate

Sentencas: But it was lower than half of the stress for the pre-sintered cell according to profile II.
Titulo: Constrained sintering of Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte on anode substrate

Sentencas: The SEM images, together with a circuit voltage of 2.22 V for two cell stack, indicate that the electrolyte of the unit cell is dense.
Titulo: Constrained sintering of Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte on anode substrate

Sentencas: The power is 41.7 W, with a power density of 0.26 W cm(-2) at 1.4 V and 750 degrees C for a two tells stacks sintered according to profile II.
Titulo: Constrained sintering of Y2O3-stabilized ZrO2 electrolyte on anode substrate

Sentencas: The ASR of the two cells stack is 2.50 Omega cm(2).
